 INSTRUCTIONS FOR PUSH NOTIFICATIONS USING FIREBASE CLOUD MESSAGING (FCM)

1: Install packages.
    i- firebase_core: ^
    ii- flutter_local_notifications: ^
    iii- firebase_messaging: ^
    iv- http: ^
    v- cloud_firestore: ^
2: Connect your app to firebase using Firebase CLI
3: Request push notifications permission.
4: Get device token generated by firebase messaging.
5: Initialize notification services of flutter local notifications(Make sure to write each and
   every permission in manifest and info.plist or other files).
6: Enable firebase cloud messaging (Project overview->Project settings->cloud messaging->cloud messaging API (legacy)).
7: Call sendPushNotification() to send notifications
8: you may need to write some metadata or intent-filter in manifest file. Do check manifest file.


